SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 42
BY SENATOR SEABAUGH
COMMENDATIONS. Commends Mike McConathy on being inducted into the 2026 class
of the Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend Mike McConathy on being inducted into the 2026 class of the Louisiana
3 Sports Hall of Fame.
4 WHEREAS, each year the Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame in Natchitoches, Louisiana
5 collaborates with the Louisiana Sports Writers Association in selecting a limited number of
6 sports figures who embody the character, skill, talent, and accomplishment worthy of being
7 named to the Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame; and
8 WHEREAS, the 2026 Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame Induction Class includes Mike
9 McConathy; and
10 WHEREAS, Mike McConathy, a native of Bossier City, has devoted more than four
11 decades of his life to the sport of basketball as a player, coach, mentor, and educator, earning
12 statewide and national respect for his leadership and dedication to student-athletes; and
13 WHEREAS, McConathy first distinguished himself as a standout athlete at Airline
14 High School, where he earned recognition as a prep All-American guard before continuing
15 his collegiate career at Louisiana Tech University; and
16 WHEREAS, while playing for the Louisiana Tech Bulldogs men's basketball team
17 from 1973 through 1977, he averaged 20.7 points per game and scored 2,033 career points,
18 earning Southland Conference Player of the Year honors as a junior and helping lead his
